snippet.textDisplay: I'm sorry, but if you think this could run on PS4 Pro game, you're wrong. Sacrifices would have to be made, mainly lowering the render resolution to 1440p. This trailer was very obviously rendered in native 4K., which PS5 will more than likely being doing. Maybe it's because I have a PC capable of running games at 4K, but I'm able spot the difference between 1440p and 4K most of the time. It's just a touch sharper, but it's definitely still noticeable. What truly makes me believe that is a PS5 game though, is the use real time ray tracing and reflections. Current consoles simply can't do that. They can just sort of fake it with screen space reflections and normal maps.
